{"questionId":"3514659","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ani opens an office equidistant from three of the cafes, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>. The equation of the perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>[</mo><mi>BC</mi><mo>]</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Complete the Voronoi diagram shown above.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/adef109a4d13b17bab6300a30b44dd9ac6274e26.png\"></p>\n<p>perpendicular bisector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AD</mi></math>: a vertical line with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> intercept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The perpendicular bisector should not go beyond the intersection point (should not enter site <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3514659","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Complete the Voronoi diagram shown above.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
